leader_title4: Minister Plenipotentiary of the Netherlands Antilles
footnote1: Papiamento is an official language in Aruba and the islands of Bonaire and Curaçao in the Netherlands Antilles. English is an official language on the islands of Saba and Sint Eustatius, as well as the island area of Sint Maarten, also in the Netherlands Antilles. Spanish, though not among the official languages, is widely spoken on the islands. In Friesland, the West Frisian language is an official language. Dutch Low Saxon and Limburgish are officially recognised as regional languages in the Netherlands.
footnote2: The Hague is the seat of the government of the Netherlands; Oranjestad is the capital of Aruba; and Willemstad is the capital of the Netherlands Antilles.
footnote3: Also .eu in the Netherlands, shared with other EU member states.
